  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Open Educational Resource and digital literacy</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Within the framework of the Knowledge Society, ICTs are a key factor that enable access and foster the reduction of obstacles and the adjustment of specifications of technological devices and applications for persons with disabilities. Despite this, it is worth emphasizing that this is not only a matter of connectivity, but rather, of competences for making the best use of information and knowledge. There is not only a gap of access, there is also a gap of contents, competencies and appropriation. In this sense, Open Educational Resources and digital literary are very useful tools to reduce this gap related to free knowledge and accessibility and competencies for the digital environment.</narrative>
  </description>
